commit.message:
runserver_plus_started signal and allow extra watched files

added runserver_plus_started signal which allows to connect
a signal just before the werkzeug server starts.

this allows to do things like:

    def watchfile(sender, **kwargs):
        path = Path(some_file)
        if not path.is_absolute():
            raise ValueError('%s must be absolute.' % path)
        sender.extra_files.add(path)

    runserver_plus_started.connect(watchfile)

added additional RUNSERVER_PLUS_EXTRA_FILES to list additional
files to watch for in settings file.

added runserver_plus_started signal which allows to connect
a signal just before the werkzeug server starts.

this allows to do things like:

    def watchfile(sender, **kwargs):
        path = Path(some_file)
        if not path.is_absolute():
            raise ValueError('%s must be absolute.' % path)
        sender.extra_files.add(path)

    runserver_plus_started.connect(watchfile)

added additional RUNSERVER_PLUS_EXTRA_FILES to list additional
files to watch for in settings file.
